# Aider configuration — {{.Project}}
#
# `.aider.conf.yml` is read every time `aider` is launched from this
# repo. The harness uses the agent-agnostic AGENTS.md (open standard,
# https://agents.md) as the single source of truth, so we pre-load it
# read-only on every Aider session — no `/read AGENTS.md` required.
#
# Aider's own docs:
#   https://aider.chat/docs/usage/conventions.html
#   https://aider.chat/docs/config/aider_conf.html

# Preload the universal harness instructions before every chat. The
# read-only flag means Aider will use prompt-caching for these files
# (Anthropic and OpenAI), so the overhead is one-time per cache TTL.
read:
  - AGENTS.md
  - CHECKPOINTS.md
  - progress/current.md

# `docs/conventions.md` carries the per-stack rules. Comment in to
# include them on every chat; leaving commented out keeps the prompt
# slim and lets the operator pull them in on demand with `/read`.
# read:
#   - docs/conventions.md

# Aider treats files matched here as "do not modify" — handy for
# protecting the feature_list state machine from accidental edits.
# Uncomment if your team wants only `korva harness *` to mutate it.
# read-only:
#   - feature_list.json
